reviews:
Initially, the flashlight that I received looked like it had been opened, stuffed back into the box, and returned. I had no proof of that, but it looked like that was the case. My knee-jerk reaction was to stuff it back into the box and return it...and request a refund. Well, my action was followed by an equal-&-opposite reaction by the Seller: Apologies, offers to replace it, more apologies. I disregarded all of them. Well, read on,

So, every now and again I'd receive another Apology w/another offer to replace the original shipment. Finally I decided I was being unreasonable, I did like the initial look of the flashlight/Offer and with all the follow-up, I finally decided to accept a replacement. It arrived a couple of days ago.

Flashlight works very well: Bright, adjustable Beam, compact design and can use 2 different power sources/Batteries.

I have given it 5-Stars for Brightness. I can't Comment on Battery life or H2O resistance... yet.
Seller has gone to great lengths to satisfy my complaints. They reached out and I, finally, accepted... and I'm glad I did.

Some Comments: If you look around amazon, you'll see several similar flashlights which may/may not be produced in the same factory somewhere.
I can recommend this Flashlight and too, I can Comment on this Seller... which I can now Recommend.

reviews:
I bought four of these for a family camping trip. The flashlight feels very sturdy and well made, being all metal except for the lens and green operational button on the bottom.

The head piece pulls in and out to change from a super-bright focused small area to a larger more dispersed area (there are no set points... you can pull it out to any level between super small and super large).

The brightness is incredible. As a focused point it's startlingly bright, and you can point it at objects very far away and light them up with ease. When focused, the light is square with some lines through it... I'm guessing the shape of the underlying LED. When you increasingly disperse the light it is still very bright, just less focused. I was looking for a very bright flashlight, and this did not disappoint.

The operation is where there is room for improvement. The green button is rubbery feeling to the touch. There are effectively 5 modes (super bright, very bright, bright, blinking fast, blinking slow). You change the modes by pressing the green button repeatedly. So the push order is:
super bright - off - very bright - off - bright - off - fast blink - off - slow blink - off (repeat).

The issue is the flashlight's memory of where you're at in that order; it always remembers your last on state, and the next time you turn it on it will go to the next one in the push order. If you want to generally use the flashlight in super bright mode, and then turn it off... the next time you turn it on it will be in very bright mode. Now you can either push the button 8 more times to get back to very bright mode (and then do it again the next time, and again, and again) or just use it in very bright mode knowing that next time you turn it on you'll be in just bright mode (and then blink mode). This is all SUPER annoying because the flashlight will NEVER, EVER be on the right setting that you want when you first turn it on, and you either need to deal with it or push the button 9 times every time you turn it on to get back to your last setting. Don't underestimate how ANNOYING this is.

Now I know that this only has one button, so they probably had to make due, but it still stinks. How it should have been designed is that if you turn it off and don't turn it back on for... oh... more than 10 seconds, it goes back to the last on state versus the next one. Maybe I'm asking too much?

--- PROS ---
- Super Duper Bright
- Heavy Duty Construction, but still fairly light in weight
- Light dispersion mechanism is smooth and works well

--- CONS ---
- Button operation is annoying as hell

review_title: Compact, BRIGHT, and lightweight. Zoom should be a feature with ALL flashlights! (*pics attached)
reviews:
This is my first tactical flashlight, and I bought it primarily for use as a bike light to mount onto my front basket. I’m using a cut-up inner tube as a mount (YAY to repurposing! 🙌).

I read a lot of reviews for tactical flashlights, prior to selecting this one, which I ultimately settled on for its price, since many customers had noted that one factory produces the same flashlight under various brand names. This one did look identical to a couple other that I was considering. They only differed in price by a couple bucks, so it ultimately depends on how much you want to save a couple bucks.

So far, it seems just fine, and is & does what it claims. I will update my review, if time and use reveal anything else.

NOTES:

* Metal body feels solid, zoom head moves smoothly, clicker button firmness good. Goldilocks approves.

* Press button VERY lightly (a slight half-press...it’s almost easy to miss) to move through the 5 light modes (high, medium, low, strobe, S.O.S.). I only “discovered” it by accident, as I’d forgotten what kind of features it had, once I placed my order. It DOES retain the memory of your last setting preference, so no need to cycle through all of them each time you turn it on (though it’s easy to inadvertently press the button more than once and prompt the next setting, but it’s a very minor & negligible matter. Once you’ve used it for a short time, muscle memory will probably take over, and you’ll know how to calibrate the firmness of your touch.).

* Small (~5” long?), lightweight, BRIGHT (*see attached pics) (requires 3 AAA batteries—not incl.)

* I can’t yet speak to the battery life or water resistance of the flashlight, but I’ll amend my review when I find out. I do know that any time you use a flashlight on a blinking mode, the batteries last considerably longer.

If I have any issues, I’ll contact the company, and most likely they’ll take care of their customers and issue a replacement, if necessary.

review_title: Super Bright, Super Wide, Super Great
reviews:
I had been looking for a tactical flashlight on a dedicated site, but thought I'd check Amazon. Positive reviews on this best seller, and a fraction of the cost lead me to make the purchase. Very glad I did.

Late last night my wife and I heard terrible cat screams from the woods behind our house, and realized one of our 3 cats was not indoors so we immediately threw 3 AAA batteries into this flashlight and ran to the creek where the screams seemed to have originated.

My wife must have commented 3 times how insanely great this flashlight is, covering such a wide swath of area, literally probably 150 degrees, seemingly more the further we had to look.

When we had an area we wanted to zoom into simply pull the lens cap out and it focusses the light onto a smaller area. She was so impressed she asked me to get one for each of our bedsides, and flashlights for the kids too.

We were unable to determine the source of the anguished sounds, but fortunately "Blackie" returned home an hour later with no knowledge we have large predators he should be aware of.

review_title: Well, it came with a gift card...
reviews:
I'm not sure if it is a marketing ruse to boost their sales, but the gift card came with instructions on how to claim it, the first being to post a five star review, and the second being to scan a bar code in order to claim it. Well, I opted for the second method and nothing materialized. The text on the gift card also claimed that I shouldn't advertise the fact that I'd received it, which made it seem like a low grade version of some publisher's clearinghouse tactic. The flashlight itself seems very good so far, with different presses of the power button producing different kinds of light. It seems to easily be worth the price so far, though. And the zoom setting really focused in on a small area, which makes it ideal for address hunting at night. So despite my reservations about the marketing ploy, and my skepticism about the authenticity of the gift card, I would have to give the flashlight itself high marks so far. Sept 8, 2020:
Ok. Now that I understand how the flashlight works, having used it for a while now, it is wonderful. It basically has four settings, slow flashing, fast flashing, and two steady settings. All settings allow for zooming, and when you focus the beam to it's most precise focus it settles on a square area which is maybe 24 inches by 24 inches, making it ideal for address finding at night, since the beam is very intense but small enough not to illuminate someone's entire picture window or anything. I use it every night with lithium batteries and it is still going strong since my purchase, so while I never actually vigorously pursued the gift card thing that came with the flashlight, it is a wonderful steal for 10 dollars. It is wonderful, and very powerful.

review_title: Great value, will be buying more!
reviews:
I'm not often motivated to write reviews - it is unusual for me to take the time to write one. That being said, I bought two of these flashlights to start off with; I figured, if it's bad, at least they're usable (as long as they make light, eh?), and if they're good, I'll buy a couple more. And I can say, I will be buying a couple more!

Great price, and for that price you get a sturdy flashlight with good quality in both construction and performance. All metal exterior, so it can take a beating. I dunked the thing in a glass of water to test its water resistance; turned it on without even drying it and it worked fine, you could literally use the thing underwater if you want. It's the perfect size, it fits nicely in your palm and is big enough to not get lost, but no bigger than it needs to be.

Everyone is talking about how bright it is, and it is indeed very bright, but what impressed me most was how massively WIDE the beam is! Standing at one end of my living room, it casts light on the entire opposite wall. If that's too much for you, simply slide the head of the flashlight outwards to narrow the beam; it narrows to less than 1/10 the size of the full beam, excellent for focusing on things.

I made a good purchase that I am quite happy with, and I will be repeating it soon so I have a few to stash in emergency kits. If you're looking for a great quality flashlight at a great price, your search is over!

review_title: Best light I've ever bought under 40$, Exceptional value for the price!
reviews:
Ok let's just start off by saying this flashlight costs under 10$ when purchased. That being said this makes all my other store bought flashlights ($5-25) seem like tealight candles in comparison! I'm currently using it with some rechargeable Samsung 18650 batteries I've had laying around for a few years but I'm sure it's the same brightness with 3xaaa.

It packs a punch of light in a small package, will blind anyone you point it at and in strobe mode it would cause anyone or anything serious pain and effect their vision for some time after.

I included photos from my yard to give you an idea of its output. I needed something to spotlight raccoons who have been trying to get at my chickens lately, my other led flashlights only reflect the eyes and create a shadow of the little pests making it hard to take a good clean shot at them. This light easy spotlights the whole creature at its wideist, when zoomed in it probably would give the raccoon sunburn and seizures, my use is about 30 yds max distance but it goes way further into the far woods.

However, giving 3 stars simply because the seller attempts to buy 5 star reviews for $10, which to me is extremely unethical. I’ve had sellers offer rewards in exchange for ANY review, which to me is more palatable, but this seller specifically says “all 5 star”. Yeah, $10 would be nice but I’d like to not contribute to false/bought reviews on amazon, since we all want to trust other peoples experiences when buying something.

In essence, so far for me it’s been a 5 star product, but just calling out the shady seller.

review_title: Not as great as many reviewers say.
reviews:
This flashlight wasn't too great. It was pesky to turn on and off because of having to toggle between the strobe setting. Also the handle broke the first time I used it on a nighttime dog walk. After the fall it began to lose brightness and didn't really offer any visibility at night thereafter.

Actually, I think so many reviewers may say that it's a five star item because they are probably compensated with a $10 Amazon credit for a 5- star review. I believe this because I received a $10 coupon for a 5-star review myself. I wanted to wait and see if this really is as good a flashlight as most everyone has said. So nstead of the credit, I'm giving an honest review: it's not worth the credit to break even on a crappy flashlight.

reviews:
EDIT:
This company told me after receiving the item, having a business card inside the box, if I did a five star rating they would issue me a $10 Amazon gift card. They specifically told me not to mention that I was doing a review. I have done everything they asked me to do including sending screenshot of my review, and emailed them three times and they finally replied that I have to download an app to my phone-in order to receive the $10 gift card.
In my opinion this is a scam.
They are complete scammers to sell their product using amazon customers.

Previous review:
What I like most about this flashlight is how powerful it is for being the perfect size. Many hand sized flashlights do not have the brightness as this one does. It feels great when holding it. Not to heavy or awkward.

It has a battery compartment that allows for the batteries to fit snug and not move around. That sure helps with the brightness staying consistent, unlike other brands without the battery compartment. Without the “compartment”, the batteries wiggle around causing the brightness to not remain strength.

The zooming lens is easy to use and a big plus, much like an “add on” feature, not to mention super handy when using it for different things. And the handle has texture to it, so it is not slippery at all. The on/off button is located at the bottom of handle and is green in color- making it easy to turn on quickly if you need it very fast for something.

It’s not cheaply made. I can’t believe it’s such a nice handy flashlight for the low cost. I highly recommend this flashlight over all others.
